:"1200","1199":"1199","1220":"1220","about 1225":"about 1225","1175":"1175","about 1200":"about 1200","1250":"1250","about 1220":"about 1220","1172":"1172","Skipness, Argyll, Scotland":"Skipness, Argyll, Scotland","Craignish, Argyll, Scotland":"Craignish, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"McSween","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Suibhne</b>, ‘son of <i>Suibhne</i>’, a Gaelic name meaning ‘pleasant, affable’, see   McQueen   1 and Irish   McSweeney  .","Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Suain</b> based on Old Norse <i>sveinn</i> ‘boy, servant’, which was also used as a personal name. This is given as the origin of the   McQueen   family of Skye (see also   McSwain   and   Whan  ) although the two similar personal names <i>Suibhne</i> and <i>Sveinn</i>, Gaelic and Scandinavian, have influenced each other more widely in Scotland."],"variants":[{"name":"Sween","meanings":["Irish and Scottish: shortened form of   McSween  .","Norwegian: variant of   Sveen  ."]},{"name":"McQueen","meanings":["Scottish and Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Shuibhne</b> ‘son of <i>Suibhne</i>’ a byname meaning ‘pleasant’. Compare   McSweeney  .","Scottish and Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Shuain</b>, a Gaelic patronymic based on Old Norse <i>sveinn</i> ‘boy, servant’, which was also used as a personal name (see   Swain  ). This is given as the origin of the McQueen or McSwan family of Skye, although the spellings are hard to distinguish. Compare   Whan  .","Americanized form of French   Moquin  ."]}]},{"name":"Miss","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname derived from the usual medieval vernacular form of   Moses  , or a revival of this form. In Wales it has in recent years also been used as a short form of Mostyn ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Miss McSween was born about 1200, in Skipness, Argyll, Scotland, her father, Dugall MacSwine, was 29 and her mother, Mrs. Dugall MacSwine, was 26. She married Dugald \"Duncan\" Campbell III Laird Craignish about 1220, in Argyll, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"about 1200–":"umbes 1200–Surnud","1200–Female":"1200–Surnud","1199–1250":"1199–1250","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1225–Male":"1225–Surnud","1172–Male":"1172–Surnud","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1225":"1225","1200":"1200","1199":"1199","1220":"1220","about 1225":"umbes 1225","1175":"1175","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1250":"1250","about 1220":"umbes 1220","1172":"1172","Skipness, Argyll, Scotland":"Skipness, Argyll, Scotland","Craignish, Argyll, Scotland":"Craignish, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1200–":"noin 1200–Kuollut","1200–Female":"1200–Kuollut","1199–1250":"1199–1250","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1225–Male":"1225–Kuollut","1172–Male":"1172–Kuollut","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1200":"1200","1199":"1199","1220":"1220","about 1225":"noin 1225","1175":"1175","about 1200":"noin 1200","1250":"1250","about 1220":"noin 1220","1172":"1172","Skipness, Argyll, Scotland":"Skipness, Argyll, Scotland","Craignish, Argyll, Scotland":"Craignish, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1200–":"environ 1200–Décédée","1200–Female":"1200–Décédée","1199–1250":"1199–1250","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1225–Male":"1225–Décédé","1172–Male":"1172–Décédé","1175–Female":"1175–Décédée","1225":"1225","1200":"1200","1199":"1199","1220":"1220","about 1225":"environ 1225","1175":"1175","about 1200":"environ 1200","1250":"1250","about 1220":"environ 1220","1172":"1172","Skipness, Argyll, Scotland":"Skipness, Argyll, Écosse","Craignish, Argyll, Scotland":"Craignish, Argyll, Écosse","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Miss McSween est née environ 1200